AmaZulu king Misuzulu KaZwelithini and Ntokozo Mayisela at the umembeso ceremony in Newcastle. DURBAN - King Misuzulu kaZwelithini has banned two members of the AmaZulu royal household from the royal coronation committee. A statement published by AmaZulu Prime Minister, Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, says princes Gibizizwe and Afrika have been excluded after claims that Prince Afrika had been appointed as the king’s spokesperson. READ: AmaZulu Royal House | King adamant he won't be dethroned The king says he has not appointed a spokesperson, despite being approached by the two princes. Buthelezi says Prince Thulani Zulu remains responsible for any matters related to royal affairs. The coronation was to have taken place at the end of May, but has been postponed due to the disruptions caused by floods in KwaZulu-Natal.